From 08a7cd8e6da5ac6ad79ba0763edf026f7bf99245 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jun Sun <jsun@junsun.net>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 13:15:16 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] virtual-device: enable RISC-V AIA in virtual_device_riscv64

AIA APLIC + IMSIC drivers landed upstream in Linux 6.10 but their
Kconfig symbols (RISCV_INTC, RISCV_APLIC, RISCV_IMSIC) are 'bool'
with no default and no platform select, so they don't get enabled by
gki_defconfig, the riscv64 defconfig, or any stock virtual_device
fragment. Add a new post_defconfig_fragment to force them =y for
cuttlefish riscv64 guests.

Without this the resulting kernel boots without IMSIC/APLIC support,
defeating the purpose of running on a 6.10+ kernel.

Change-Id: I0c539867d814ebc46af4a11325e6864b13e6fa62
Signed-off-by: Jun Sun <jsun@junsun.net>
---
 BUILD.bazel          |  1 +
 riscv64_aia.fragment | 20 ++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 riscv64_aia.fragment

diff --git a/BUILD.bazel b/BUILD.bazel
index 71efe75..fb2dff6 100644
--- a/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/BUILD.bazel
@@ -744,6 +744,7 @@ kernel_build(
     post_defconfig_fragments = [
         "virtual_device_core.fragment",
         "virtual_device.fragment",
+        "riscv64_aia.fragment",
     ],
     strip_modules = True,
     visibility = ["//common-modules:__subpackages__"],
diff --git a/riscv64_aia.fragment b/riscv64_aia.fragment
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..883fdf5
--- /dev/null
+++ b/riscv64_aia.fragment
@@ -0,0 +1,20 @@
+# Enable RISC-V Advanced Interrupt Architecture (AIA).
+#
+# AIA APLIC + IMSIC drivers landed in upstream Linux 6.10 (May 2024) but the
+# Kconfig symbols are bool with no default and no platform-level select, so
+# they are NOT enabled by gki_defconfig, the riscv64 defconfig, or any of the
+# stock virtual_device.fragment files. Required for cuttlefish-on-riscv64
+# guests that boot under crosvm/QEMU with AIA topology in DT.
+#
+# Source of truth for these driver files:
+#   drivers/irqchip/irq-riscv-intc.c
+#   drivers/irqchip/irq-riscv-aplic-{main,direct,msi}.c
+#   drivers/irqchip/irq-riscv-imsic-{early,platform,state}.c
+CONFIG_RISCV_INTC=y
+CONFIG_RISCV_APLIC=y
+CONFIG_RISCV_IMSIC=y
+
+# Disable -Werror for kernel module compiles (matches arm.fragment).
+# Without this, clang -Warray-bounds in include/linux/signal.h's
+# _SIG_SET_BINOP dead-code branches fails the build under riscv64.
+# CONFIG_WERROR is not set
-- 
